    "body": "I started using [something like that](https://github.com/kmcallister/html5/blob/86333c33f23a77e70c95522cf3fd9a0c8ce37eb5/src/tree_builder/mod.rs#L363-L405) in another part of the library.  In this style, the example above would become\n\n``` .rs\nmatch chars.next() {\n    '/' => { self.state = EndTagOpen; }\n    c if match c.to_ascii_opt() {\n        Some(a) => { do_something(a.to_lower()); true }\n        _ => false,\n    } => (),\n    c if other_condition => { ... }\n    _ => parse_error()\n```\n\nWhich is sort of weird, but easy enough to get used to.\n",
